üèÜ Completing TryHackMe or Hack The Box Learning Paths ‚Äî Extended Description
Overview

TryHackMe and Hack The Box are online platforms that provide hands-on cybersecurity labs and challenges. Completing their structured learning paths allows learners to develop skills in:

Network scanning & enumeration

Web application exploitation

System & network exploitation

Active Directory security

Capture the Flag (CTF) challenges

Defensive security (Blue Team exercises)

These platforms are widely recognized in cybersecurity portfolios and are excellent preparation for certifications like OSCP, CEH, or Security+.

1Ô∏è‚É£ Understanding the Platforms
TryHackMe (THM)

Beginner-friendly with guided rooms and detailed instructions

Focuses on step-by-step learning

Offers learning paths, e.g.:

Complete Beginner ‚Üí Cyber Defense ‚Üí Offensive Security

Linux Fundamentals ‚Üí Windows Exploitation ‚Üí Active Directory

Hack The Box (HTB)

More advanced, realistic penetration testing environment

Focuses on realistic lab machines and challenges

Offers Learning Paths / Academy courses such as:

Penetration Testing Essentials

Linux Exploitation

Windows Active Directory

Web App Security

Both platforms provide certificates of completion for learning paths ‚Äî great for portfolios.

2Ô∏è‚É£ Recommended Learning Path Strategy
Step 1: Build Foundation

Learn basic Linux & Windows commands

Understand networking fundamentals (TCP/IP, ports, protocols)

Study basic security concepts: firewalls, encryption, common attacks

Step 2: Beginner Labs

On THM:

Complete rooms like: ‚ÄúLinux Fundamentals,‚Äù ‚ÄúIntro to Cybersecurity,‚Äù ‚ÄúBasic Pentesting‚Äù

On HTB Academy:

Courses like ‚ÄúNetwork Fundamentals,‚Äù ‚ÄúLinux Privilege Escalation,‚Äù ‚ÄúWeb Application Security‚Äù

Step 3: Core Skills

Enumeration: Nmap, Netcat, SMB enumeration

Exploitation: Metasploit, manual exploitation techniques

Web Security: SQLi, XSS, LFI/RFI, authentication bypass

Windows Security: Active Directory exploitation, password attacks

Linux Security: File permissions, privilege escalation, cron jobs

Step 4: Capture the Flag Challenges

Solve THM CTFs or HTB retired machines

Document steps in a write-up (port scanning, enumeration, exploitation, post-exploitation)

Step 5: Advanced Topics

Exploit development basics

PowerShell & Bash scripting for attacks

Red Team / Blue Team scenarios

Defensive measures: IDS/IPS, logs, SIEM, endpoint protection

3Ô∏è‚É£ Lab Documentation & Portfolio Integration

For each lab or machine, document:

Objective: What the lab teaches

Tools Used: Nmap, Metasploit, Burp Suite, etc.

Commands & Screenshots: Step-by-step workflow

Findings & Exploits: Open ports, vulnerable services, password hashes

Lessons Learned: Security implications, defensive strategies

Screenshots: Highlight key steps and results

Optional Write-ups: Host on GitHub or personal portfolio

Example: Document your HackTheBox retired machines on GitHub with screenshots and command outputs.

