5Ô∏è‚É£ Tools and Resources for Labs

VMs & Lab Environment: VirtualBox or VMware

Attacker VM: Kali Linux

Defensive VM: Windows Server, Linux Server, AD lab

Security Tools:

Nmap, Netcat, Wireshark

Metasploit Framework

Burp Suite, OWASP ZAP

John the Ripper, Hydra

Documentation Tools: Markdown, GitHub, Obsidian, Notion

6Ô∏è‚É£ Learning Outcomes

By completing THM or HTB learning paths, you will gain:

Practical cybersecurity skills for offensive and defensive roles

Hands-on experience with realistic penetration testing scenarios

Portfolio-ready projects including lab write-ups and CTF solutions

Understanding of network security, vulnerabilities, and exploit mitigation

Preparation for cybersecurity certifications

7Ô∏è‚É£ Tips for Success

Practice consistently ‚Äî even 1‚Äì2 machines per week builds expertise

Always document your process with screenshots and notes

Start with TryHackMe if new, move to HackTheBox for realistic labs

Work on retired machines for portfolio write-ups

Use virtual labs to avoid impacting production or external networks

Challenge yourself with time-bound CTFs to simulate real penetration testing scenarios

